						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab standing in Survey No. 539.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1635.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1557, Yuva, Āshāḍa, ba. 13, Thursday, corresponding to 1635 A.D., July 2.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription, in Nāgari characters and Marāṭḥī language, seems to record a fight between <hi rend="bold">Pādas11āhi Suḷatāna Mahamada Arakā[ḍa] and</hi> <hi rend="italic">rājādhirāja</hi> <hi rend="bold">Murāri Paṇḍit[ēs11vara]</hi> on the bank of the <hi rend="bold">Bhīmarathī</hi> near <hi rend="bold">Dēvaṇagāu.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
